pace","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Observations consist of positional values of different body parts of the ant,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"followed by the velocities of those individual parts (their derivatives) with all"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the positions ordered before all the velocities."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"By default, observations do not include the x- and y-coordinates of the ant’s torso. These may"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be included by passing "},{"code":"exclude_current_positions_from_observation=False","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" during construction."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In that case, the observation space will have 113 dimensions where the first two dimensions"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"represent the x- and y- coordinates of the ant’s torso."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Regardless of whether "},{"code":"exclude_current_positions_from_observation","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" was set to true or false, the x- and y-coordinates"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the torso will be returned in "},{"code":"info","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" with keys "},{"code":"\"x_position\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"\"y_position\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", respectively."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, by default, an observation is a "},{"code":"ndarray","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" with shape "},{"code":"(111,)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"where the elements correspond to the following:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Num","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Observati